"v.(使)潮湿；使沮丧，泼凉水 【英】 v. (使)潮湿(to make damp; moisten)使沮丧，泼凉水(to deaden, depress, reduce, or lessen) 【考】 assuage : sorrow / dampen : ardor(抚慰使痛苦减少/使 沮丧使热情减少) 【记】 来自damp(潮湿的)+en →使…潮湿 【例】 Nothing can dampen my spirits on this glorious morning. v. 使潮湿 = moisten; 使沮丧, 泼凉水 = deaden = depress = reduce 【类】assuage: sorrow = dampen: ardor = alleviate: strength抚慰减少痛苦 = 使沮丧减少热情 = 减轻强度 【反】scorch(v 烧焦; 枯萎); damper(n 抑制因素)－amelioration(n 改进) 【记】dam + 音：破，泼，大坝破了，大坝泼水会潮湿；damp + en 使→使潮湿 dampen (v.)  1630s, ""to dull or deaden"" (of force, enthusiasm, ardor, etc.), from damp (adj.) + -en (1). Meaning ""to moisten"" is recorded from 1827. Related: Dampened; dampening."
